<h2>The weather in December 2020</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
December 2020 was warmer than the 1981-2010 average for December over much of Europe, but temperatures were close to or slightly below average over Ireland and the Iberian peninsula. Temperatures were considerably higher than average over Norway, Sweden and Finland. December 2020 was also much milder than usual over and to the north of the Balkans.
